<TITLE> Burglars steal Tk 1 crore in city </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 26 (bdnews24.com)  Burglars allegedly broke into offices of two business firms at Mohakhali DOHS area and stole money and valuables worth over one crore taka on Wednesday night, ahead of the Eid-ul-Azha vacation. The gang stole Tk 1 crore in cash from the office of GMS Composite Knitting Industries Ltd and Tk 10 lakh in cash and valuables worth Tk 5 lakh from an office of Altranet Group on the second floor of a building. Kafrul Police Station sub-inspector Arshidul Haque told bdnews24.com they were investigating into the burglary. Chief accountant of GMS Composite Knitting Industries Ltd, Md Ahsanul Haque said they had left the office after 8pm on Wednesday. "After coming to the office this morning we saw the main gate was locked. Then we found the back door broken. And when we opened the locker we found Tk 1.0 crore was missing," he said. The money was withdrawn to pay the employees of the company their salaries and Eid bonus, Haque said. Altranet Group chief Qazi Ehteshamul Haque said the burglars had taken away money and valuables worth Tk 15 lakh. The building's caretaker Zafar Ali said one tenant, who lives on the fourth floor, had come to the house with his four friends. The guests left the house after midnight, he said. 
